        </div>

        <!-- Do & Don't Section -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="do-dont" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Default type for links inside body copy.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Standalone type for call-to-action links outside paragraphs.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use WithIcon type when an icon adds meaningful context.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Primary style as default for standard navigation links.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Danger style only for irreversible or destructive actions.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Underline = Always inside body text.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Underline = HoverOnly for standalone or grouped links.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Keep link labels concise and descriptive.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use TextLink as a substitute for a Button when the action doesn't navigate.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use Subtle style in body text where contrast alone won't distinguish it.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use Underline = None in flowing text.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use vague labels like "click here" or "read more".</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't mix multiple link styles within the same sentence.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use Danger style for standard navigation.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use WithIcon type inside dense body text.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div> <!-- End tab-overview -->

      <!-- ======= STYLE TAB ======= -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-style" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="variant-axes" class="doc-section-title">Variant Axes</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">TextLink supports a combinatorial variant space spanning 864 unique configurations.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>3 Type</strong> &times; <strong>4 Style</strong> &times; <strong>4 State</strong> &times; <strong>3 Size</strong> &times; <strong>3 Underline</strong> &times; <strong>2 RTL</strong> = <strong>864 variants</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="types" class="doc-section-title">Types</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Three layout types control the link's visual form and placement context.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Use case</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Default</strong></td><td>Inline text link with no icons. Renders inside body copy.</td><td>Inline navigation within paragraphs.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Standalone</strong></td><td>Link placed outside body copy with a trailing chevron.</td><td>Call-to-action links, section footers.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>WithIcon</strong></td><td>Text link with leading and/or trailing icons.</td><td>External links, contextual navigation.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="styles" class="doc-section-title">Styles</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Four visual styles communicate semantic intent and visual emphasis.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Style</th><th>Color</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Primary</strong></td><td><span style="color:#2C66DD; font-weight:600;">#2C66DD</span></td><td>Accent blue. Standard links and primary navigation.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Secondary</strong></td><td><span style="color:#5F6C89; font-weight:600;">#5F6C89</span></td><td>Muted color. Lower emphasis supporting links.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Subtle</strong></td><td><span style="color:#1A1A2E; font-weight:600;">#1A1A2E</span></td><td>Body text color. Use sparingly where underline provides distinction.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Danger</strong></td><td><span style="color:#C1181B; font-weight:600;">#C1181B</span></td><td>Red. Destructive or irreversible actions.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="states" class="doc-section-title">States</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Four interaction states provide visual feedback throughout the user journey.</p>
          <div class="state-grid">
            <div class="state-card">
              <a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-md link-underline-always" onclick="return false;" style="justify-content:center;">Default</a>
              <div class="state-card-title">Default</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Standard resting state</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <a href="#" class="link-demo link-md link-underline-always" style="color:#1E52BB; justify-content:center;" onclick="return false;">Hover</a>
              <div class="state-card-title">Hover</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Darkened color on mouse over</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-md link-underline-always link-focus" onclick="return false;" style="justify-content:center;">Focus</a>
              <div class="state-card-title">Focus</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">2px solid focus ring</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-md link-underline-always link-disabled" onclick="return false;" style="justify-content:center;">Disabled</a>
              <div class="state-card-title">Disabled</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">50% opacity, no interaction</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="sizes" class="doc-section-title">Sizes</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Three sizes for different layout densities. Medium is the default.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Size</th><th>Font Size</th><th>Icon Size</th><th>Preview</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Small</strong></td><td>12px</td><td>12px</td><td><a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-sm link-underline-always" onclick="return false;">Small link</a></td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Medium</strong> (default)</td><td>14px</td><td>14px</td><td><a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-md link-underline-always" onclick="return false;">Medium link</a></td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Large</strong></td><td>16px</td><td>16px</td><td><a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-lg link-underline-always" onclick="return false;">Large link</a></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="underline-behavior" class="doc-section-title">Underline Behavior</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Three underline modes control text decoration across states.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Mode</th><th>Behavior</th><th>Guidance</th><th>Preview</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Always</strong></td><td>Underline visible in all states</td><td>Use inside body text for maximum discoverability.</td><td><a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-md link-underline-always" onclick="return false;">Always visible</a></td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>HoverOnly</strong></td><td>Underline appears on hover</td><td>Use for standalone or grouped links.</td><td><a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-md link-underline-hover" onclick="return false;">Hover to see</a></td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>None</strong></td><td>No underline in any state</td><td>Use only when context makes the link obvious (e.g., navigation menus).</td><td><a href="#" class="link-demo link-primary link-md link-underline-none" onclick="return false;">No underline</a></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="design-tokens" class="doc-section-title">Design Tokens</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Color and typography tokens used by the TextLink component.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Value</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>text-link-primary</code></td><td>#2C66DD</td><td>Primary style default color</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-link-primary-hover</code></td><td>#1E52BB</td><td>Primary style hover color</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-link-secondary</code></td><td>#5F6C89</td><td>Secondary style default color</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-link-subtle</code></td><td>#1A1A2E</td><td>Subtle style default color</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>text-link-danger</code></td><td>#C1181B</td><td>Danger style default color</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>focus-ring</code></td><td>2px solid #2C66DD</td><td>Focus outline for keyboard navigation</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>underline-offset</code></td><td>3px</td><td>Gap between text baseline and underline</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ======= USAGE TAB ======= -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When to Use</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">TextLink is the standard component for text-based navigation actions.</p>
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
              <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                When to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For inline navigation within body text or paragraphs.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For standalone call-to-action links outside body copy.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For contextual links with icons pointing to external resources.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">For secondary navigation elements in footers, sidebars, or lists.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
              <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
                When NOT to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">When the action does not navigate (use a Button instead).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For primary page actions that should visually stand out (use Button).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">When the link destination is ambiguous or lacks clear context.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="type-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Type Guidelines</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Choose the right type based on context and placement.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Default (Inline):</strong> Use for links embedded within paragraphs or body text. Always pair with <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Underline = Always</code> for discoverability.</li>
            <li><strong>Standalone:</strong> Use for call-to-action links that live outside of flowing text. Pair with a trailing chevron to indicate actionability.</li>
            <li><strong>WithIcon:</strong> Use when an icon adds semantic meaning (e.g., external link, download). Avoid in dense body text to maintain readability.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="rtl-support" class="doc-section-title">RTL Support</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">TextLink supports full right-to-left rendering for languages like Arabic and Hebrew.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>When <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">RTL = True</code>, the entire link layout mirrors: leading icon moves to trailing position and vice versa.</li>
            <li>Text direction is set to <strong>auto</strong>. All spacing and alignment values are mirrored.</li>
            <li>Underline behavior remains consistent across both directions.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="related-components" class="doc-section-title">Related Components</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used alongside the TextLink.</p>
          <div class="related-grid">
            <a href="Button.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"/></svg> Button</a>
            <a href="Icon.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/></svg> Icon</a>
            <a href="Navigation-bar.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 12h18M3 6h18M3 18h18"/></svg> Navigation bar</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="figma-reference" class="doc-section-title">Figma Reference</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Access the design source file for the TextLink component.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Figma Node:</strong> <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">17646:374198</code> -- Component Set: TextLink</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

